1. Season the eggs. Whisk them with a bit of salt.
2. Stir-fry the onions and garlic. Set them aside.
3. Cook the eggs. Quickly stir-fry / scramble the eggs in a bit of vegetable oil( or butter) until they're just set. Add them to your bowl of onions.
4. Heat a little butter, then fry the rice by spreading it in a hot pan. Let the rice fry undisturbed for a few minutes, then toss it around a bit and let it fry again. Repeat this about four times.
5. Bring it all together! Carrots, eggs - just add them frozen, they'll warm up as you incorporate them. If still needs salt, add to taste and then it's time to eat!